<item>
            <title>[HIVE-24023] Hive parquet reader can&apos;t read files with length=0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-24023</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Impala truncates insert-only parquet tables by creating a base directory containing a completely empty file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hive throws an exception upon reading when it looks for metadata:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Error: java.io.IOException: java.lang.RuntimeException: &amp;lt;file&amp;gt; is not a Parquet file (too small length: 0) (state=,code=0)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can introduce a check for an empty file before Hive tries to read the metadata.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
